@node "Main" "Welcome to WarpNeoPocott"

@{jcenter}@{fg shine}WarpNeoPocott 0.38@{fg text}

@{jleft}  Welcome to WarpNeoPocott for Amiga WarpUP systems!

  WarpNeoPocott is a port of a WIP Neo Geo Pocket Colour emulator, a lovely little handheld console which unfortunately seems to take second place to the GameBoy.  :-(  Written by Julien Frelat (AKA Gollum), it is the first of a number of handheld console emulators, including GameBoy Colour.  Checkout http://neopocott.emuunlim.com for more information!

  @{"Usage" link "Usage"}

  The latest version of WarpNeoPocott can be found at http://www.powerup.com.au/~cward

  If you have any problems with this program, feel free to contact me at cward@powerup.com.au.

@{jcenter}@{fg shine}Code HQ - Never surrender - Amiga always!

@endnode

@node "Usage"

@{jcenter}@{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}

@{jleft}  WarpNeoPocott is launched in the standard manner for WES engines, using the WES parameter "-neopocott."  See WES.guide for more details.

  @{fg shine}Keyboard@{fg text}

  In game keys are as follows:-

  Cursor keys - Guess!  :-)
  Ctrl = Button A
  Shift = Button B
  Tab = Option
  P = Pause
  F3 = Reset

  The keys were chosen on the basis of them being either logical (cursor keys) or familiar (F3 = Reset in WarpMAME).

  @{fg shine}Joystick@{fg text}

  The Joystick is also supported, although it doesn't need too much explaining.  :-)  However, if you have a CD32 controller and lowlevel.library then Red = Button A and Blue = Button B.  In the absence of lowlevel.library, only the blue button will work.

@{jleft}

@endnode
